          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>Single folio parchment Qurʾān manuscript with the shelfmark  M.2002.1.375. Qurʾān text: Q Q 70:27-71:6. At the moment only the image of   the fol 1 verso is given by the institution. The outer margins of the  parchment are damaged. </p>
              <p>There are three  other folios in the same collection, that originally belonged to the  same codex: M.2002.1.350, M.2002.1.351 and M.2002.1.374. </p>
              <p>The four sister fragments arranged according to the Qurʾānic text they cover: </p>
              <p>
                <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/verse-navigator/sura/31/verse/19/manuscripts/1527">(1) Q 31:14-25, M.2002.1.350.</ref>
              </p>
              <p>
                <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/verse-navigator/sura/54/verse/31/manuscripts/1517">(2) Q 54:31-55:8, M.2002.1.351.</ref>
              </p>
              <p>
                <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/verse-navigator/sura/68/verse/43/manuscripts/1523">(3) Q 68:29-69:4, M.2002.1.374.</ref>
              </p>
              <p>
                <hi rend="bold">(4) Q 70:27-71:6, M.2002.1.375. </hi>
              </p>
              <p> Cf. the website of the institution: <ref target="https://collections.lacma.org/node/205190">https://collections.lacma.org/node/205190</ref>. </p>
            </summary>
            <msItem xml:id="mysql_id_687860" n="1v">
