          <physDesc>
            <objectDesc>
              <supportDesc material="parchment">
                <support>
                  <p>Verse division and illumination: Simple verse separators consist of a  group of three small strokes arranged one above the other. Tenth verse  separator consists of a golden medallion ornament with the <hi rend="italic">abǧad-</hi>numeral placed inside the circle. On <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/verse-navigator/sura/70/verse/42/manuscripts/1532/page/1v">fol. 1v</ref> a band ornament in geometrical pattern with cross-shaped elements in gold red and blue ink is dividing the sūrahs, that fills out the whole line.  </p>
                  <p>Short strokes were used at the end of a line to fill out the space. </p>
                </support>
              </supportDesc>
              <layoutDesc>
                <layout writtenLines="16">16 - 16 lines to a page
                                </layout>
              </layoutDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc>
              <handNote/>
            </handDesc>
            <scriptDesc>
              <summary>
                <p>Script style kūfi B.II with some variations. The letter <hi rend="italic">ʾalif </hi>slightly bands to the right. The tail of the letter <hi rend="italic">ʿayn </hi>in the final position extends generously. The <hi rend="italic">lām-ʾalif </hi>ligature has more resemblance with the shape seen in the B.Ib style. </p>
                <p>Diacritical marks are used sparsely and are indicated by oblique strokes. Vocalisation is marked by red and blue (?) dots.  </p>
              </summary>
              <scriptNote>
                                                                kūfī B.II
                            </scriptNote>
            </scriptDesc>
